==English==

===Noun===
'''logorrhea''' (''US'')
# (''medical'') An excessive and often uncontrollable flow of words.
# (''humorous'') Excessive talkativeness.

===Alternative spellings===
*[[logorrhoea]] (''British'')

====Synonyms====
*(2): [[verbal diarrhea]]


=== Information ===
Logorrhea was the winning word of Nupur Lala in the 1999 Scripps National Spelling Bee.

